
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-bess-evpn-vpws-14.txt'>
    <title>"Virtual Private Wire Service support in Ethernet VPN", Sami Boutros, Ali Sajassi, Samer Salam, John Drake, Jorge Rabadan</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-bess-evpn-vpws-14.txt</link>
    <description>This document describes how Ethernet VPN (EVPN) can be used to support Virtual Private Wire Service (VPWS) in MPLS/IP networks. EVPN enables the following characteristics for VPWS: single-active as well as all-active multi-homing with flow-based load-balancing, eliminates the need for Pseudowire (PW) signaling, and provides fast protection convergence upon node or link failure.</description>
    <dc:date>2017-05-15T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
